HEADWORD: Mohur
<hw>Mo"hur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind., fr. Per.
<ets>muhur</ets>, <ets>muhr</ets>, a gold coin, a seal, seal
ring.]</ety> <def>A British Indian gold coin, of the value of fifteen
silver rupees, or $7.21 (in 1913).</def> <rj><au>Malcom.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
